Introduction

Jinhong is a former member of the Korean boy group 24K and was the former maknae of AA. He joined AA in 2013 at the age of 15 after Juwon left the group. However, in 2015, Jinhong left AA and joined 24K under Choeun Entertainment. His membership in 24K was confirmed at the end of May 2015, following a performance of "Hey You," where Jinhong and Hui disguised their identities with masks.

In 2017, Jinhong and other 24K members participated in YG Entertainment's survival series MIXNINE. However, after leaving 24K in 2019, Jinhong withdrew from the entertainment industry. In 2022, he made a brief return, appearing in the music video for "Cheese Burger" by his former groupmate Kisu.
